The Easter weekend rush is in full swing and more than 17 000 vehicles have already passed through the N1 toll gate in the Western Cape on Thursday, according to Western Cape Provincial Traffic Chief Kenny Africa. Africa said this during a briefing on the provinces state of readiness ahead of the Easter Long Weekend. “We are expecting a busy Easter weekend in the province,” said Africa. “If we catch you speeding, driving under the influence of alcohol and drugs, we will arrest you,” he added. Africa also urged motorists to adhere to the speed limit. This morning, Minister of Transport Blade Nzimande and Mayor of Tshwane, Solly Msimanga handed out car seats to motorists while promoting road safety at the N1 petroport North Bound. -TNA Reporter